  "text": "The distance used is either Euclidian or Manhattan distance. The concept of absolute core point was also proposed in [CITATION_1] where it is called special core point. In the definition of an absolute core point s, there is at least one core point within the range of s w.r.t E and Minpts. So we also add the furthest core point within the range of s w.r.t E and Minpts in the first part of our local representative. Briefly, this first part is R x which includes clusters representative R x containing their set of pair (absolute core point s, its farthest touchable core point c s ):",
